'''Josef "Harry" Jelinek''' (1905-1986) was a Czech [[con artist]] and publisher of Nazi propaganda, who is reputed to have fraudulently sold the [[Karlštejn|Karlštejn Castle]] to American industrialists in 1945.<ref name=CzechTV>{{cite web|last1=Jan|title=Legendární podvodník – neváhal prodat Karlštejn ani vydat český Mein Kampf|url=http://www.ceskatelevize.cz/ct24/exkluzivne-na-ct24/210532-legendarni-podvodnik-nevahal-prodat-karlstejn-ani-vydat-cesky-mein-kampf/|website=www.ceskatelevize.cz|publisher=Česká televize|accessdate=24 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140624203812/http://www.ceskatelevize.cz/ct24/exkluzivne-na-ct24/210532-legendarni-podvodnik-nevahal-prodat-karlstejn-ani-vydat-cesky-mein-kampf/|archivedate=24 June 2014|deadurl=no|date=13 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=Langley1>{{cite web|last1=Claxton|first1=Matthew|title=I may have a bridge to sell you|url=http://www.langleyadvance.com/opinion/editorial/i-may-have-a-bridge-to-sell-you-1.670136|website=langleyadvance.com|publisher=Glacier Community Media|accessdate=24 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140624202808/http://www.langleyadvance.com/opinion/editorial/i-may-have-a-bridge-to-sell-you-1.670136|archivedate=24 June 2014|deadurl=no|date=24 October 2013}}</ref><ref name=RadioPraha1>{{cite web|last1=Velinger|first1=Jan|title=Victor Lustig - the man who (could have) sold the world|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/czechs/victor-lustig-the-man-who-could-have-sold-the-world|website=www.radio.cz|publisher=Radio Praha|accessdate=24 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313214437/http://radio.cz/en/section/czechs/victor-lustig-the-man-who-could-have-sold-the-world|archivedate=13 March 2014|deadurl=no|date=15 October 2003}}</ref>
==Biography== Jelinek was born 14 October 1905 in the town of [[Vlašim]], [[Czechoslovakia]] (now a part of the Czech Republic).<ref name=CzechDictionary>[http://www.slovnik-nakladatelstvi.cz/osobnosti/harry-jelinek.html Czech Dictionary]</ref> He died in [[Guarene d'Alba]], Italy in 1986.<ref name=CzechDictionary />
